{
  "texts": [
    "(d) Support Vector MachineA Support Vector Machine (SVM) is a supervised machine learning technique utilized for both classification and regression tasks [27].",
    "Its primary efficacy lies in binary classification scenarios where the objective is to categorize data points into two classes based on their inherent features [77].",
    "SVMs are rooted in principles encompassing linear algebra, optimization theory, and the notion of identifying an optimal hyperplane that effectively distinguishes data points [38].",
    "Here's a breakdown of the fundamental mathematical principles underpinning SVMs [109].• Hyperplane: In a two-dimensional space, a hyperplane is akin to a line that separates two data classes.",
    "As dimensions increase, the hyperplane becomes a flat affine subspace, like a plane in three dimensions."
  ]
}